Tony Blair and Oracle’s Larry Ellison are pushing digital ID in Britain, with Blair’s Institute funded by millions from Ellison while lobbying for centralized health and population data. Behind the glossy promises of safety and efficiency lies something darker — the consolidation of information, power, and control. Is this progress, or the architecture of a digital cage?
